address: Thị trấn Khoái Châu, Huyện Khoái Châu, Tỉnh Hưng Yên
thought:
**Mapping an Old Vietnamese Address to New Administrative Units**

Okay, so I've got this Vietnamese address to map: "Thị trấn Khoái Châu", "Huyện Khoái Châu", "Tỉnh Hưng Yên". My first step is to break down the old administrative components: the ward, district, and province. Easy enough. Now, the real fun begins.

I'll start with the province. I know mergers are a thing in Vietnamese administrative history, so I'll quickly check if "Tỉnh Hưng Yên" has been affected. The "60-NQ/TW" resolution is my go-to for these changes. Ah, good, "Tỉnh Hưng Yên" remains "Tỉnh Hưng Yên". Crisis averted there.

Next, I need to delve into the ward-level changes. I'll scour the "Other resolutions" focusing on "Thị trấn Khoái Châu." And there it is, resolution "1666/NQ-UBTVQH15"! Line 18 is the golden ticket: it explicitly states that "Thị trấn Khoái Châu" will be merged with several other communes to form the new "**xã Khoái Châu**". Bingo!

Now, the final step: validating this new ward's existence and data. I'll search through my "New wards" list for "xã Khoái Châu."  Perfect! `{"ward_code":"12205","ward_name":"Xã Khoái Châu","province_name":"Tỉnh Hưng Yên"}` matches.  The province name also aligns.

My confidence here is sky-high. The resolution directly outlines the merger, and the new ward data confirms its existence and location.  I'm ready to package this up into a clean JSON output, ready to go.

citation.line: 18. Sắp xếp toàn bộ diện tích tự nhiên, quy mô dân số của thị trấn Khoái Châu và các xã Liên Khê, Phùng Hưng, Đông Kết thành xã mới có tên gọi là xã Khoái Châu.
